gov.va.med.srcalc.domain.calculation

Class CalculationResult

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.va.med.srcalc.domain.calculation.CalculationResult
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public final class CalculationResult
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

    A calculation result. Stores both the calculation input values and the outcomes. Immutable as long as the provided Value objects are immutable.

    Per Effective Java Item 17, this class is marked final because it was not designed for inheritance.

    • Constructor Detail

      • CalculationResult

        public CalculationResult(org.joda.time.DateTime startDateTime,
                 int patientDfn,
                 java.lang.String specialtyName,
                 java.util.Set<Value> values,
                 java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Double> outcomes)

        Constructs an instance with the given properties.

        Note: does not perform any consistency check on the data. For example, this constructor will accept outcomes for models not in the given specialty.

        Parameters:
        startDateTime - when the calculation was started, for metrics
        patientDfn - the associated patient DFN
        specialtyName - the associated specialty name, must not be null
        values - the calculation input values, must not be null. The passed collection may be mutable as this object will take an immutable snapshot.
        outcomes - the calculation outcomes, must not be null. The passed collection may be mutable as this object will take an immutable snapshot.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if any argument is null or any value in a collection argument is null
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the given values set contains multiple ProcedureValues
